The paper deals with the problem of Simultaneous Localisation and Mapping (SLAM) using visual data, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses techniques from observer design, which is a subfield of control theory (cs.SY). The use of visual data suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new observer design, which could be of interest to the machine learning community (cs.LG) and the artificial intelligence community (cs.AI).
